DuPont Co. has sold thin-film panels
for a solar project in  India , according to a statement.  DuPont Apollo, a unit of the Wilmington, Delaware-based
chemical maker, supplied the panels to Yantra eSolar India Pvt.,
owner of the 5-megawatt project in western Gujarat state,
according to an e-mailed statement today from DuPont.  The statement didnâ€™t provide a value of the deal. The plant
in Charanka village is scheduled to be connected to the
electricity grid by August, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
